name: Amy Dowden
summary: Strictly Come Dancing star Amy Dowden has faced a new cancer scare, jeopardizing her return to the show. Dowden, who previously overcame thyroid cancer, is now awaiting results after discovering a lump in her breast. The news has brought support from fellow Strictly stars, and Dowden has shared her experiences to raise awareness about the importance of self-examinations. Despite her health challenges, Dowden remains determined to return to the show and is receiving treatment to address her condition.

name: Jamie Smith

summary: Charley Hull, a professional golfer, has been making headlines with her participation in the AIG Women's Open. Despite facing criticism from "trolls," Hull remains unfazed and focused on her performance. She has taken an early lead in the competition, despite windy conditions. Hull's tee times have been announced, placing her alongside Nelly Korda and Lilia Vu at St Andrews. Notably, Hull has revealed that she is suffering from degenerative arthritis, a condition that affects her physical abilities. Despite this, she took a one-shot lead after the opening round and is considered a potential European hope for success at the tournament. Hull's determination to prove her worth is evident, particularly against Nelly Korda, a formidable opponent. With three rounds remaining, Hull and Lilia Vu are chasing Korda's three-shot lead, aiming to secure the championship title.
